1
00:00:05,130 --> 00:00:10,360
Great job. You've taken your first steps in visualizing your data.

2
00:00:10,360 --> 00:00:14,080
In this lesson, you'll learned about the plots and code that you can use to

3
00:00:14,080 --> 00:00:17,835
visualize and understand individual variables in your data set.

4
00:00:17,835 --> 00:00:21,120
For quantitative variables, the most common plot type is

5
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:23,965
the histogram and for qualitative variables,

6
00:00:23,965 --> 00:00:26,605
the most common plot type is the bar chart.

7
00:00:26,605 --> 00:00:29,190
You learned about the limitations of pie charts and

8
00:00:29,190 --> 00:00:32,170
doughnut charts and how they can be used effectively.

9
00:00:32,170 --> 00:00:34,900
You also learned about techniques to help you identify

10
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:37,780
trends in the data and deal with outliers.

11
00:00:37,780 --> 00:00:39,425
On the vertical axis,

12
00:00:39,425 --> 00:00:41,510
you learned how to report frequencies in terms of

13
00:00:41,510 --> 00:00:44,390
absolute counts or as relative frequencies.

14
00:00:44,390 --> 00:00:47,920
For quantitative data, you also learned how to set parameters in

15
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:52,430
